HEADWORD: Succedaneous
<hw>Suc`ce*da"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>succedaneus</ets>. See <er>Succeed</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to,
or acting as, a succedaneum; supplying the place of something else;
being, or employed as, a substitute for another.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

